oai_dc:dc.dc:title: District IV
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Lovell, William L.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: I received forty-three (43) questionnaires from the veterinarians in the four states of Michigan, Ohio, West Virginia, and Kentucky. Twenty-three (23) replied that they do not and have not used animal technicians in their practices. Nineteen (19) have and are using lay employees trained by the veterinarian as animal technicians. One (1) is using a formally trained technician in his large animal practice.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1974; 88
